button.buyMore.description: Button text, allowing users to purchase more credits.

button.uploadReferences.description: Button text, allowing users to upload references.

button.success.description: Button text, indicating operation was successful.

button.generating.description: Button text indicating an operation is in progress

button.failed.description: Button text indicating an operation has failed

button.download.description: Button text allowing the user to download results

button.fast.description: Button text allowing the user to set 'Fast mode' to quickly generate images

button.relax.description: Button text allowing the user to set 'Slow mode' to relax and generate images

button.turbo.description: Button text allowing the user to set 'Turbo mode' to generate images

button.more.description: Button text allowing the user to view more options

button.generate.description: Button text allowing the user to generate images

button.history.description: Button text allowing the user to view the history of generated images

button.generateNew.description: Button text allowing the user to create a new image

field.finalPrompt.description: Final painting prompt used to generate images

field.elements.description: Painting style used to generate images

field.traceId.description: Trace identifier for tracking image generation requests, do not translate, keep as 'Trace ID'

description.aspect.message: --aspect, change the aspect ratio of generated images, default values depend on the model and mode

description.chaos.message: --chaos, adjust the degree of variation in generated images, higher values produce more unique and unexpected images, range 0-100, default is 1

description.fast.message: Ignore current settings, run a single generation task under 'Fast mode', no default value

description.iw.message: --iw, set the importance of image prompts relative to text prompts during generation, range 0-2, default is 1

description.no.message: --no, instructs the generation system to attempt excluding certain elements, e.g., '--no plants' tries to generate images without plants, no default value
description.no.description: Description of exclude parameter, translate to 'ÊéíÈô§'

description.quality.message: --quality, set the quality and rendering time of generated images, range .25, .5, or 1, default is 1

description.random.message: Add random basic style codes to prompts, can use '--style random-16', '--style random-64', or '--style random-128' for different lengths of random style effects, no default value

description.relax.message: Override current settings, run a single task under 'Slow mode', no default value

description.repeat.message: --repeat, create multiple tasks from a single prompt, range 1-40, default is 1

description.seed.message: --seed, initial visual noise for generated images, range 0-4294967295, default is randomly generated

description.stop.message: --stop, halt tasks at any stage of the generation process, range 10-100, default is 100 (full generation)

description.style.message: --style, switch between different versions or styles of Midjourney or Niji models, e.g., raw, cute, expressive, original, scenic, default values depend on the model and mode

description.stylize.message: --stylize, adjust the intensity of default aesthetic styles applied during generation tasks, range 0-1000, default is 100

description.tile.message: --tile, generate images suitable for creating seamless tiling, no default value

description.turbo.message: Override current settings, run a single task under 'Turbo mode', no default value

description.weird.message: --weird, exploring unconventional aesthetic styles with a range from 0-3000, defaulting to 0

description.translation.message: Enable automatic translation during generation, non-Chinese content will be translated to English input for Midjourney

description.imageWeight.message: --iw, adjusts the weight of image prompts relative to text prompts, ranging from 0-2, defaulting to 1

description.niji.message: --niji, when enabled, generates images using the Niji model for an anime-style image

description.uploadReferences.message: Upload images as references for generation, supports up to 5 images. If more than 1 image is uploaded, they will be automatically merged

description.raw.message: --raw, when enabled, generates images using the Midjourney model for an original style image

description.prompt.message: Enter command, additional parameters will override default settings. For example, adding '--stylize 200' will force the final command to use '--stylize 200'

action.generate.message: Click this button to start image generation

action.variation1.message: Adjust variation of the first image

action.variation2.message: Adjust variation of the second image

action.variation3.message: Adjust variation of the third image

action.variation4.message: Adjust variation of the fourth image

message.promptPlaceholder.message: Enter a phrase describing the image you want to generate, e.g., a cute cat. Additional parameters will override default settings

message.uploadReferencesExceed.message: Can only upload up to 5 images
message.uploadReferencesExceed.description: Error message when exceeding upload limit

message.uploadReferencesSuccess.description: Success message when images are successfully uploaded

message.uploadReferencesError.message: Failed to upload image, please try again later
message.uploadReferencesError.description: Error message when image upload fails

message.startingTask.description: Message when drawing task is starting

message.startTaskSuccess.description: Success message when drawing task starts successfully

message.startTaskFailed.description: Error message when unable to start drawing task

message.noOperations.description: Message when no operations are available

message.noTasks.message: No historical tasks, please start a new task first
message.noTasks.description: Message when no historical tasks are available

model.general.description: Model name used for general image generation

model.niji.description: Model name used for anime-style image generation, do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.model.description: Name of the model used in machine learning for image generation

name.aspect.description: Name of the aspect ratio parameter

name.chaos.description: Name of the chaos level parameter, translate to 'Chaos level'

name.fast.description: Name of the fast mode, used for quick image generation, translate to 'Fast mode'

name.nijiStyle.description: Name of the nijiStyle parameter, do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.imageWeight.description: Name of the image weight parameter

name.no.description: Name of the exclude parameter, used to exclude specific elements, translate to 'Exclude'

name.quality.description: Name of the quality parameter, used for setting the quality of generated images

name.mode.description: Name of the mode parameter, used for setting the speed of image generation

name.random.description: Name of the random parameter, used for adding random style effects

name.relax.description: Name of the relax mode, used to generate images in 'slow speed' mode, translate to 'Relax mode'

name.repeat.description: Name of the repeat parameter, used to create multiple tasks from one prompt

name.seed.description: Name of the seed parameter, used to set initial visual noise

name.stop.description: Name of the stop parameter, used to stop the task at any stage

name.style.description: Name of the style parameter, used to switch between different versions or styles of models

name.stylize.description: Name of the stylize parameter, used to adjust the intensity of default aesthetic styles

name.tile.description: Name of the tile parameter, used to generate images suitable for tiling

name.turbo.description: Name of the turbo mode, used to generate images in 'turbo' mode, translate to 'Turbo mode'

name.weird.description: Name of the weirdness parameter, used to explore unusual aesthetic styles, translate to 'Weirdness'

name.translation.description: Name of the translation parameter, used to enable automatic translation during generation

name.advanced.description: Name of the advanced mode, used to enable advanced mode

name.niji.description: Name of the niji parameter, used to enable the Niji model, do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.ignore.description: Name of the ignore parameter, used to ignore certain elements

name.prompt.description: Name of the prompt parameter, used for inputting drawing instructions

name.raw.description: Name of the raw parameter, used to enable the Midjourney model

placeholder.prompt.message: Enter a sentence describing the image you want to generate, e.g., a cute cat. Additional parameters will override default preset parameters
placeholder.prompt.description: Placeholder text in the prompt field

placeholder.ignore.message: Enter elements to ignore, e.g., `--ignore plants`

status.pending.description: Status of a task - not yet started
